In addition to the "Carl Vinson", the U.S. aircraft carriers currently cruising in the Pacific Ocean include the "USS Abraham Lincoln" aircraft carrier that departed from the United States on January 3.
The Lincoln also carried the F-35C carrier squadron for the first time, which is part of the U.S. Marine Corps' 314th Fighter Strike Squadron.
In addition to the above-mentioned two aircraft carriers, the U.S. Navy currently deploys the USS Ronald Reagan aircraft carrier in Yokosuka, Japan.
The carrier battle group also includes the guided-missile cruiser USS Lake Champlain and the guided-missile destroyer USS Stockdale.
