Chatting with friends about the recent 26% drop in Meta, and the market value has evaporated by 251 billion US dollars, Zuckerberg responded that "faced with unprecedented competition", why?
Meta (formerly Facebook) is essentially an advertising company, and its revenue mainly comes from advertising. The advertising companies that make money today have their own traffic channels.
Facebook, Instagram, Whatsapp, etc., no matter what kind of functional positioning, are Meta's traffic channels.
Not only that, Meta is also the largest "advertising alliance", and many apps have external Meta advertisements, which are realized through Meta's advertising platform.
However, times have changed.
First, due to the adjustment of Apple's privacy policy, it is difficult for Meta to obtain user data information, which affects the efficiency of advertising.
Apple's current privacy policy is very user-friendly, and it will clearly prompt users whether to allow the app to obtain their own information. The normal reaction of most people is definitely not to allow it.
Next, if Google stabs another knife, the impact on Meta's revenue will be even greater.
Second, the China factor in Meta's revenue growth in the past has also weakened (the proportion of this factor is uncertain, but it does exist).
Everyone usually knows that Meta has no business in China, but this understanding is not accurate.
At least 10% of Meta's revenue comes from China every year, mainly contributed by Chinese companies that do overseas business.
Meta's office in Hong Kong is about several hundred people, and there are several major agents in mainland China.
Chinese companies want to expand overseas markets, Meta is an inescapable advertising channel, and most of the money they burn is given to Meta.
Interestingly, Byte's TT is now one of Meta's main competitors, but Meta made a lot of money from Byte in the first two years.
All domestic agents are helping Byte to advertise in Meta, and Meta's performance in Greater China is also very good.
I haven't looked into it specifically lately, but it's definitely not better than before.
The stage of Chinese companies burning cash overseas on a massive scale is over.
Third, the expansion of new traffic channels is not smooth.
Facebook is getting older and newer platforms, including TT, are not in Meta's hands.
The biggest problem isn't just declining revenue, it's the lack of growth expectations.
The capital market is not only looking at income, but more importantly, what is expected in the future.
Clearly, Meta's expectations were not enough.
To tell a new story to the market, Zuckerberg told the "metaverse".
The metaverse should indeed be one of the future directions, but the realization cycle of the metaverse is relatively long, and this story should not be enough to support the market value of Meta in two or three years.
So the next two years should be a difficult period for Meta.
Don't look at Facebook's current popularity. It also has an annual revenue of 100 billion to 200 billion US dollars. In fact, Facebook has a very strong sense of crisis now. Compared with other Internet companies and high-tech companies, there is no good security moat.
Although several of his social software now have relatively high daily activities and are also mainstream social software, such as Facebook, WhatsApp, etc., but in the face of the rapid development of tiktok, Facebook has no confidence, and the subversion is the blink of an eye.
As for the elusive concept of the metaverse, there is absolutely no hope of success in a short period of time, so Facebook is very dangerous, which is why Zuckerberg changed the name of the company and kept looking for it. The root cause of the new track, but I think his track choice is wrong, it is a road of no return The above are some of my thoughts for reference.
Article 17 The state implements a registration practice management system for the qualifications of registered fire engineers.
Persons who have obtained the qualification certificates of the first-level and second-level registered fire engineers can practice in the name of the corresponding level of registered fire engineers.
Article 18 The Fire Department of the Ministry of Public Security is the registration approval department for the qualification of a first-class registered fire engineer.
The fire department of the public security organ of the province, autonomous region, and municipality directly under the Central Government is the registration approval department for the qualification of the second-level registered fire engineer, and is responsible for the preliminary examination of the registration of the first-level registered fire engineer.
Article 19 Those who have obtained the first-level or second-level registered fire engineer qualification certificates and apply for registration shall be employed by an approved fire protection technical service organization or key fire safety unit, and shall report to the location of the unit through the employing unit (the employing unit belongs to the place where the unit is located). If it is an enterprise, submit the registration application materials to the fire department of the public security organ in the place where the industrial and commercial registration is located) through the enterprise.
Article 20 After receiving the registration application materials from the applicant, the fire protection department of the public security organ of the province, autonomous region or municipality directly under the Central Government shall notify the applicant at one time on the spot or within 5 working days if the application materials are incomplete or do not conform to the statutory form. If the applicant fails to inform all the content that needs to be supplemented and corrected within the time limit, the application will be accepted from the date of receipt of the application materials.
For registration applications that are accepted or rejected, a written certificate affixed with the special seal of the fire department of the public security organ at the same level and dated shall be issued.
Article 21 The fire protection agencies of the public security organs of the provinces, autonomous regions and municipalities directly under the Central Government shall, within 20 working days from the date of accepting the registration application, complete the preliminary examination of the application materials for the qualification registration of the first-level registered fire engineer and the second-level registration according to the prescribed conditions and procedures The registration and approval of fire engineer qualifications, and the application materials and preliminary review opinions for the first-level registered fire engineer qualification registration shall be submitted to the Fire Department of the Ministry of Public Security for approval.
The fire department of the Ministry of Public Security shall make a decision on whether to approve or not within 20 working days from the date of receipt of the application materials and preliminary examination opinions submitted by the fire department of the provincial public security organ.
If the approval decision cannot be made within the prescribed time limit, the applicant shall be informed of the extended time limit and the reasons.
If the decision of disapproval is made, the reasons shall be explained in writing, and the applicant shall be informed of the right to apply for administrative reconsideration or file an administrative lawsuit according to law.
Article 22 The registration examination and approval department shall issue and serve the registration certificate of the corresponding level within 10 working days from the date of making the approval decision.
Article 23 Each registration of the registration certificate is valid for 3 years.
The registration certificate is the practice certificate of the corresponding level of registered fire engineer within the validity period, which shall be kept and used by the registered fire engineer himself.
Article 24 To apply for initial registration, an application shall be filed within one year from the date of obtaining the first-level and second-level registered fire engineer qualification certificates.
Late applications for initial registration must meet the continuing education requirements of this regulation.
The specific measures for registration management such as initial registration, renewal of registration, change of registration, cancellation of registration and non-registration shall be separately prescribed by the Ministry of Public Security.
Article 25 Continuing education is a necessary condition for the renewal of registration, re-registration and overdue initial registration of registered fire engineers.
Within the validity period of each registration, registered fire engineers at all levels shall complete corresponding continuing education in accordance with regulations.
Article 26 The registration examination and approval department shall promptly announce to the public the registration of registered fire engineers, establish integrity files of registered fire engineers, and implement credit management for their practice activities.
Article 27 The registration management departments for the qualifications of registered fire engineers at all levels shall strictly implement the relevant provisions of the "Administrative License Law of the People's Republic of China".
